---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '@components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | RHT: Reading Habit Tracker"
  description="Privacy policy for RHT, the Reading Habit Tracker mobile app."
>
  <main class="page-wrap">
    <a href="/rht" class="back-link">&larr; Back to RHT</a>

    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: July 2026</p>

    <p>
      <strong>RHT: Reading Habit Tracker</strong> keeps your reading life on your
      device. There are no accounts, no analytics, no ads, and no tracking. Your reading
      data is never uploaded anywhere by us. The app makes exactly two kinds of network
      requests, described below.
    </p>

    <h2>Your Reading Data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Reading logs, streaks, books, and settings are stored in a local
        database on your device
      </li>
      <li>Nothing is synced to a cloud and there is no account to create</li>
      <li>
        You can export everything as a JSON file from Settings at any time; the
        export is created on demand and shared only where you choose to send it
      </li>
      <li>
        Deleting the app deletes your data; Settings also offers a full reset
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Book Search (Open Library)</h2>
    <p>
      When you search for a book, the text of your search is sent to Open
      Library (openlibrary.org, a project of the Internet Archive) to find
      matches, and book covers are fetched from covers.openlibrary.org. Like any
      web request, these include your IP address. They include nothing about you
      or your reading history, and RHT attaches no identifiers. If you never use
      search, no request is made. See the <a
        href="https://archive.org/about/terms.php"
        >Internet Archive's privacy policy</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h2>App Updates</h2>
    <p>
      To deliver bug fixes between store releases, the app checks Expo's update
      service (EAS Update, operated by Expo) for a newer version of its code,
      automatically at launch and when you tap "Get the latest bug fixes" in
      Settings. These requests include technical details needed to serve the
      right update: platform, app runtime version, and update channel. They
      include no personal data and none of your reading data. See <a
        href="https://expo.dev/privacy">Expo's privacy policy</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h2>Notifications</h2>
    <p>
      The optional daily reminder is a local notification scheduled entirely on
      your device. Notification content never leaves your device.
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics and Advertising</h2>
    <p>
      None. RHT contains no analytics, no advertising, and no third-party
      tracking of any kind.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy changes, the updated version will be posted at this address
      with a new date above.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions about this privacy policy, contact: <a
        href="mailto:amanmittal.work@gmail.com">amanmittal.work@gmail.com</a
      >
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  body {
    background: linear-gradient(
      180deg,
      #fce8c9 0%,
      #fdf6eb 35%,
      #ffffff 100%
    ) !important;
  }
</style>

<style>
  .page-wrap {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 24px 40px;
    font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
    color: #1d1d1f;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #6e6e73;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .back-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    color: #1d1d1f;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 6px;
    letter-spacing: -0.3px;
  }

  .updated {
    color: #86868b;
    font-size: 13px;
    margin: 0 0 32px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 28px 0 10px;
    color: #1d1d1f;
  }

  p {
    color: #6e6e73;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    padding-left: 18px;
    list-style: disc;
  }

  li {
    color: #6e6e73;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  a {
    color: #b45309;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  a:hover {
    color: #92400e;
  }
</style>
